{"title": "Captain Billy's Whiz Bang, Vol. 3, No. 27, November, 1921", "description": "\"Captain Billy's Whiz Bang\" was an iconic magazine of wit and humor launched by W.H. Fawcett in 1919. Each 64-page issue was packed with jokes, quips, and humorous bits of writing. Each year it grew in popularity, and Fawcett\u2019s success lead to the formation of the well-known Fawcett Publications, which issued Whiz Comics and introduced Captain Marvel. The magazine was immortalized in a line in the song \u201cTrouble\u201d from Meredith Willson\u2019s \u201cThe Music Man.\u201d This issue has articles such as, \"Movie Hotstuff,\" \" Sporty New Orleans,\" \" Limber Kicks', \"and many short quips, plus the usual departments are here such as, Drippings from the Fawcett, Pasture Pot Pourri, and Smokehouse Poetry - Summary by Larry Wilson", "duration": 6751, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "16036", "name": "W. H. Fawcett"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/whizbangv3n27_2602_librivox/capt_billys_whizzbang3_30_2602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1921", "genres": ["Humor"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Larry Wilson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "lomond"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whizbangv3n27_2602_librivox/whizbangv3o27_00_fawcett_64kb.mp3", "duration": 81}, {"section": 1, "title": "Drippings From the Fawcett", "readers": [13374], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whizbangv3n27_2602_librivox/whizbangv3o27_01_fawcett_64kb.mp3", "duration": 437}, {"section": 2, "title": "Short Quips", "readers": [13374], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whizbangv3n27_2602_librivox/whizbangv3o27_02_fawcett_64kb.mp3", "duration": 493}, {"section": 3, "title": "Questions and Answers", "readers": [20469], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/whi